  "texts": [
    "IntroductionVisual autoregressive (VAR) models [21,26,35,59,61,83,85] have recently emerged as strong competitors to diffusion and flow models for image generation, achieving comparable image quality.",
    "Until recently, the inherent unidirectional bias of autoregressive models [58] was considered inadequate for capturing bidirectional correlations among image patches.",
    "However, a recent breakthrough in VAR lies in shifting the prediction paradigm from next-token prediction to next-scale prediction.",
    "VAR represents an image as a pyramid of latent patches, structured from the lowest resolution (a single coarse patch) to progressively higher resolutions.",
    "Within each level, VAR generates patches jointly, while across levels, finer-scale patches are generated autoregressively, conditioned on the previously generated coarser level."
  ],
